										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-43802" src="http://dummy.umy.ac.id/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Screen-Shot-2020-10-15-at-14.04.23.png" alt="" width="4096" height="2304" /><span title="">After being held for 2 days, the 2020 International Conference on Sustainable Innovation (ICOSI) was officially closed.</span> <span class="" title="">The closing ceremony was held virtually on Wednesday afternoon (14/10) through the Microsoft Team platform and Youtube streaming broadcast live from the Meeting Room, Floor Floor.</span> <span class="" title="">5, AR Fachruddin B Building, Universitas Muhammadiyah Yogyakarta (UMY).</span></p>
<p>Ari Kusuma Paksi, Ph.D, vice chairman of the ICOSI 2020 executive through his remarks expressed his gratitude to the participants who participated in this conference. &#8220;We are honored that you have trusted us, ICOSI, as a platform to share your research results,&#8221; he said. Ari added that even though we are in the middle of a pandemic, this conference was successfully held virtually.</p>
